Put the eggs, milk, flour, cocoa and a pinch of salt in a bowl. Whisk everything with a whisk to create a smooth batter.

Grease a hot pan with oil, pour a little batter on it and spread it evenly over the entire surface of the pan. Fry on both sides until golden brown. Fry as many pancakes as there is batter.
How to fry really thin pancakes

Whisk a smooth cream from the mascarpone, cream and sugar.

Start assembling the cake. Place the pancake on a plate, spread with cream, drizzle with Nutella and cover with another pancake, repeating the process. Continue assembling until you have pancakes.

Spread the last pancake with cream and sprinkle with cocoa. Decorate with flowers and fruit.
